Ford GoBike Data Analysis¶

Nima Afshar¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

Bay wheels was primarily a public bicycle sharing system in California which started working in 2013 as "Bay Area Bike Share". After 5 years in 2018 it had over 2,600 bicycles in 262 stations around San Fransisco, East Bay and San Jose. From 2017, Ford Motor company took partnership and company been renamed to Ford GoBike. After Motivate's acquisition by Lyft, the system was renamed to Bay Wheels in June 2021.

Bay Wheels fleets has two types of bicycles, 1. classic docked model and 2. hybrid model wich can be parked either at a dock or even without that. Both types of bicycles had contactless smart card reader. they are available 24/7 which can be hired by customer in different way( single hire, annual membership etc) single rides start at \$3 per ride and can be up to 159 for annual membership.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶¶

  • trip duration: how long the trip took in seconds
  • start and end time, start, end date, time for the bikers.
  • stations: start,end station, name
  • Customer data: gender, birth date and user type
  • rented bikes: bike id

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

  • trip duration

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

  • members age
  • start time
  • gender
  • user type
  • special pattern associated with a specific group of riders

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?¶

  • Rides on Saturday and Sunday have longer trip durations compared to other days.
  • The mean trip duration of bikers at 8 AM and 3 PM is higher than the mean trip duration at other times of the day.
  • The mean trip at 4 AM has the least trip duration.
  • Female bikes a bit longer on average compared to male.
  • Customer has a wider range of trip duration and the mean duration of subscriber is less than the mean duration of customers.

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?¶

  • In general male user are more than felame users. The amount of users on Saturday and Sunday are less than the other days of the week which can be concluded that bikes more get used in order to go work during the weekdays.
  • The mean age of the bikers are similar during the week,
  • The mean age of the bikers are similar during the weekend
  • mean age of bikers on Saturday and Sunday are less then the mean age of bikers on the other days of a week.
  • Male subscriber and male customers are more than female sunscriber and female customers.

In [52]:
plt.suptitle('Hourly Usage during the week for members gender')
plt.figure(figsize= (16,8));
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
customers = df_new.query('member_gender == "Male"')
ct_counts = customers.groupby(['start_time_day', 'start_time_hour']).size()
ct_counts = ct_counts.reset_index(name='count')
ct_counts = ct_counts.pivot(index='start_time_day', columns='start_time_hour', values='count')
sb.heatmap(ct_counts, cmap='inferno_r');
plt.title('Male', loc='right');
plt.xlabel('Hour of Day');
plt.ylabel('Day of Week');

plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
subscribers = df_new.query('member_gender == "Female"')
st_counts = subscribers.groupby(['start_time_day', 'start_time_hour']).size()
st_counts = st_counts.reset_index(name='count')
st_counts = st_counts.pivot(index='start_time_day', columns='start_time_hour', values='count')
